
Caramel
=======

Caramel is an Open Source Mobile Operating System based on Objective-C frameworks, including GNUstep, Chameleon, and WebKit. 

Installation
------------

1. Read:

	resources/GNUstep-manual.pdf

2. For information about gcc, objective-c, GNUstep, makefiles, check the URLs of this file:

	resources/README

3. The instructions in frameworks/README are based on Linux Ubuntu, to install Ubuntu:

	http://www.ubuntu.com

- To make vim as your default editor:

	~$ sudo vim .bashrc

- Add these lines at the end:

	export EDITOR=vim
	export GNUSTEP_MAKEFILES=/usr/share/GNUstep/Makefiles

4. To run Ubuntu as a virtual machine inside Mac OSX:

        http://www.tuaw.com/2009/09/07/how-to-set-up-ubuntu-linux-on-a-mac-its-easy-and-free/

- Choose "Fixed size storage" and not "Dynamically expanding storage"

- You might want to put the size for the Hard disk to be 10 GB instead of the default 8 GB.

- In order to be able to ssh from mac to Ubunut virtual machine:

4.1 In VirtualBox goto from the menu VirtualBox > Preferences > Network, then click the icon to add a network.

4.2 Click Settings > Network, click "Adapter 2" , choose Attached to: "Host-only Adapter", click Ok.

5. Install gnustep from Linux Ubuntu:

        ~$ sudo aptitude -y install gnustep gnustep-devel

- Check if it is installed properly:

	~$ cd /usr/lib
	/usr/lib$ ls -lh libgnu*

- You should see:

	-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 6.9M 2011-06-20 08:49 libgnustep-base.a
	lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   23 2011-06-20 08:49 libgnustep-base.so -> libgnustep-base.so.1.22
	lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   25 2011-06-20 08:49 libgnustep-base.so.1.22 -> libgnustep-base.so.1.22.0
	-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 4.5M 2011-06-20 08:49 libgnustep-base.so.1.22.0
	-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 7.4M 2011-08-29 05:47 libgnustep-gui.a
	lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   22 2011-08-29 05:46 libgnustep-gui.so -> libgnustep-gui.so.0.20
	lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root   24 2011-08-29 05:46 libgnustep-gui.so.0.20 -> libgnustep-gui.so.0.20.0
	-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 4.4M 2011-08-29 05:47 libgnustep-gui.so.0.20.0

6. Compile and test caramel/examples. Follow instructions in:

	examples/README

7. Follow the step by step instructions for installation of GNUstep, Caramel, and Chameleon frameworks:

	frameworks/README

